<font color="#FF0000">MY OPINION OF THIS WEBSITE</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jan 24 11:39:38 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To all here:<br>
     I have a few comments on the dialog I've seen here.<br>
1.  This unsupervised discussion is a waste of cyberspace.  People have said things here that in person would have probabely landed them a punch in the face.  The age of electronics has made &quot;below the belt&quot; comments possible.<br>
2.  With all the misunderstandings and personal attacks, one would think this is a third grade classroom argument, instead of a frank discussion between adults.<br>
3.  People here are claiming to be things they are not.  They are people claiming to be Doctors, Veterans, experts and many other thinks.  Undounbtly many of these people are what they say they are and come here in earnest for answers, only to find this space polluted by liars and foul people looking to fight.<br>
4.  This many years after the war, I doubt it is unlikely many of us will be convinced or have their opinions swayed by others to a new direction is unlikely.  Those of us that served (myself included  I was in Nam in 1970), as with those that didn't have have formed a set of observations and opinions that are not really going to change on the basis of the dialog here.<br>
5.  As a college graduate, educator and a person trained in the field of psychology, I see a dialog as this to be detrimental instead of helpful.  There are many other supervised bulletin boards and discussions, which are more<br>
able to help the Vet heal and remember and the student learn.  I have had my students visit this site initially, butr now I don't recommend it.  I have returned once again to having local Vietnam Vets like myself come to the class from the Veterans of Foreign Wars post.  Even though I am sure their are genuine vets here with good intentions, I don't take the risk of having impostors talk about a war they know nothing about to my students.<br>
6.  Did anyone notice that those seeking info are often ignored.  Also, have you noticed the same few people are always on these dialogs here?  Ever notice how instead of understanding and an open mind, many here are closed minded and argumentative, making these discussions personal attacks?<br>
7.  I'm sure this post will illicit, horrible responses and accusations about my agenda and background.  Let me answer those responses now: No, I don't have any agenda!  Yes, I am a credible Nam Vet that is in his right mind. IF you don't have to prove your a Nam Vet here, then I don't either (it is not fair-but I don't have any way of knowing if you are a Nam vet either), I am sorry for the the students and others that have come here to learn or heal, try the website-SOCIAL history of Vietnam War -it's moderated!!!  All your harsh words have no effect on me, I've heard them before!!  For my true veteran brothers, come join us in the discussions offered by one of the many veterans organizations-From Vietnam Vets of America to the helicopters pilot's association.  You will be welcomed with open minds and kind hearts.<br>
Thanks for your time and concern!!!  <br>
One last note-this is my opinion, I fought in Nam for the right to it, No one can take it away from and I will not be silenced by personal petty attacks.  If you want to attack me personally for what I said, grow up!!  Just like the Gunnery sergeant said &quot;This is America, Love it or Leave It!!&quot; 
<p><code>--   (Thomas R. Brody ) </code><p>


